premise_source_doc_sentence: The Specsavers National Book Awards , or simply National Book Awards -- previously known as the Galaxy National Book Awards  (  2010 -- 11  )  ; British Book Awards or Nibbies  (  1990 -- 2009  )  -- is a British literary award for the best UK writers and their works , as selected by an academy of members from the British book publishing industry .
Prior to 2010 , it was known as the British Book Awards and was promoted by the UK publishing industry trade journal Publishing News .
In May 2017 , the British Book Awards returned , presented by The Bookseller .

The shortlists are created by around 50 individuals from the National Book Awards Academy , who are drawn from retailer chain buyers , independent booksellers , wholesalers and trade press columnists .
The criteria for a winning book is primarily the appeal , profile and sales impact of the title concerned .
